### Variables — replace with your actual tokens
# Consumer token and emplyee token set in user settings

@baseUrl = https://tripletex.no/v2

### Create session token (production)
# @name createSession
PUT {{baseUrl}}/token/session/:create?consumerToken={{consumerToken}}&employeeToken={{employeeToken}}&expirationDate=2026-03-10

### Extract session token from response
@sessionToken = {{createSession.response.body.$.value.token}}

### Test authentication — list projects
GET {{baseUrl}}/project?from=0&count=5
Authorization: Basic 0:{{sessionToken}}

### List employees
GET {{baseUrl}}/employee?from=0&count=5
Authorization: Basic 0:{{sessionToken}}

### List recent timesheet entries
GET {{baseUrl}}/timesheet/entry/>recent?count=5
Authorization: Basic 0:{{sessionToken}}

### Create session token (test environment)
# PUT https://api-test.tripletex.tech/v2/token/session/:create?consumerToken={{consumerToken}}&employeeToken={{employeeToken}}&expirationDate=2026-03-10
